            <thetext>Consider a toolbar with many buttons to manipulate the content of the HtmlArea. Whenever any button is clicked and this button is setup with the properites &quot;focusable: false&quot; and &quot;keepFocus: true&quot; the HtmlArea won&#39;t loose the focus and executes the commands correctly.
IE browsers however do not support so-called &quot;inactive selections&quot;. Only one visible selection is supported for the whole browser. This is especially an issue if an application developer provides a textfield to enter a URL to insert into the editor. If the user selects a portion of text to create a hyperlink this will fail since IE does loose the selection / range to operate on whenever the user focuses the textfield.

Offer a public API to store the range to later operate at this.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
